HEADWORD: Single-acting
<hw>Sin"gle-act`ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having
simplicity of action; especially <fld>(Mach.)</fld>, acting or exerting
force during strokes in one direction only; -- said of a reciprocating
engine, pump, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

